{"type":"message","id":"c94173ba","parentId":"efe660c2","timestamp":"2026-03-30T09:23:59.734Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_19b72ee6da0a4869b1e17e91","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-03-30\n\nSession started at 12:25 AM Europe/Ljubljana. Completed startup sequence: read SOUL.md, USER.md, MEMORY.md. Greeted user as bbymama. User said \"hi\", responded with friendly greeting and ask how to help. User then said nothing else; we continued conversation asking what they want to work on.\n\nUser requested to remove writing restrictions/format demands. Identified restrictions in SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, and AGENTS.md regarding mandatory double line breaks on Telegram. Provided ideas for visual improvement using emojis, bold, italics, and visual markers. User approved approach.\n\nUpdated all three files:\n- Removed rigid double line break requirements\n- Added flexible formatting guidelines emphasizing clarity\n- Included double line breaks as recommended for readability\n- Guidelines now suggest: emojis, **bold**, *italics*, visual markers (•, ✅, 🚀, 💡), double line breaks between paragraphs/lists, horizontal rules (---) for sections, concise sentences\n\nUser task completed successfully.\n\nLater, user requested quick check-in on projects and incompletes. Reviewed memory logs and workspace:\n- Completed: Notion Integration (API connected, database with 14 tasks, live progress, organized scripts)\n- Completed: Workspace Setup (full .md file structure, bot identity bbymama, user profile, memory system)\n- Completed: Organization (cleaned root, moved scripts, deleted redundant files)\n- Focus Areas: Vibe coding (OpenClaw), Agentic AI (OpenCode), Bot building (Antigravity), Automations\n- 12-Month Goal: First income stream (still exploring)\n- Incomplete/Next Steps: Ship something real, go deep on one stack (OpenClaw suggested), learn to prompt better, find first $1 idea\n- Bottom Line from Advice: \"Stop setting up. Start shipping.\"\n\nUser then asked about YouTube Research skill status. Checked:\n- Skill files present in skills/youtube-research/\n- SKILL.md documentation complete\n- Search script functional (python3 skills/youtube-research/scripts/youtube_search.py --help works)\n- YouTube API key configured in .env\n- Test search for \"OpenClaw\" returned result: Fireship video \"The wild rise of OpenClaw...\" from 2026-01-30\n- YouTube Research skill appears operational for search and video details\n- Transcript extraction requires yt-dlp (not tested yet)\n\nLater, user requested to add yt-dlp to the skill folder and update SKILL.md. We:\n1. Copied yt-dlp from ~/.local/bin/yt-dlp to skills/youtube-research/scripts/\n2. Made it executable\n3. Modified youtube_search.py to prefer the bundled yt-dlp in the scripts folder before falling back to system yt-dlp\n4. Updated SKILL.md to reflect that yt-dlp is bundled and provide installation options\n\nLater, user expressed interest in exploring transcription options. We discussed free API options and decided to add offline transcription using the Vosk library. We:\n- Added --transcribe-offline flag to the script\n- Implemented transcribe_audio_with_vosk() function that:\n   * Checks for Vosk installation\n   * Uses a bundled or user-specified Vosk model (default: vosk-model-small-en-us-0.15 in skills/youtube-research/vosk_models/)\n   * Downloads audio via yt-dlp\n   * Converts audio to mono 16k PCM wav using ffmpeg\n   * Performs speech recognition and returns transcript with word-level timestamps\n- Updated SKILL.md with requirements for Vosk, installation instructions, and usage example\n- Updated Quick Start section to show the new command\n\nLater, user requested to install vosk. We:\n1. Installed Vosk via pip: `pip install vosk --break-system-packages` (successful)\n2. Created model directory: skills/youtube-research/vosk_models\n3. Downloaded vosk-model-small-en-us-0.15.zip (41MB) from alphacephei.com\n4. Extracted the model\n5. Moved the extracted model folder to skills/youtube-research/scripts/vosk_models/ to match the script's expected path\n6. Tested offline transcription with the OpenClaw Fireship video (ssYt09bCgUY) using the command:\n   `python3 skills/youtube-research/scripts/youtube_search.py --video ssYt09bCgUY --transcribe-offline`\n   The transcription succeeded, producing a rough but recognizable transcript of the video (word count ~1,261). The output showed the Vosk model loading and processing logs, followed by the transcript.\n\nAll requested updates are complete. The YouTube Research skill now supports:\n- Search and video details (unchanged)\n- Caption-based transcript extraction (using bundled yt-dlp)\n- Offline audio transcription (using Vosk model)\n\nDisk space usage: Vosk model ~50MB, yt-dlp bundle ~5MB, plus original skill files.\n\nNext steps for the user: They can now use `--transcribe-offline` on any YouTube video to get an auto-generated transcript via Vosk (English model). For other languages, they would need to download appropriate Vosk models and optionally set VOSK_MODEL_PATH.\n\nUser task completed successfully."}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774862639732}}
